If two resistors, R_1 and R_2, in an electrical circuit are connected in parallel, the total resistance R in the circuit is given by \frac{1}{R}=\frac{1}{R_1}+\frac{1}{R_2}
Suppose that the second resistor, R_2, is 10 ohms greater than the first. Express 1/R as a single fraction in terms of R_1.
Write an expression for R as a function of R_1.

Show that
\frac{1}{v}=\frac{1}{V}+\frac{K}{Vs} 
is another form of the Michaelis-Menten equation. (See Problem 49.)
